#Two options to upload template file with SQL commands

## Using pg_read_binary_file sql function

Using this option the user must first copy the file into the postgresql data folder. To find this path use the command "show data_directory"
According to documentation (https://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.2/functions-admin.html#FUNCTIONS-ADMIN-GENFILE) only files within the database cluster directory and the log_directory can be accessed.

- docker cp file_name container_name:/var/lib/postgresql/data/
- insert into files values
  (nextval('files_seq'), null,'Sample_document.docx',pg_read_binary_file('sample_reference.docx')::bytea,'SUBMITTED',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'1 kB');
- insert into reference_files values
  (currval('files_seq'), 'Sample_document.docx', 'TASK_TEMPLATE_FILE');

## Convert a file to base64 and use decode

Using this option the user must first use a tool to convert a file in base64 string and use the decode function to store it as binary in the database.

Running 'base64 -w 0 <filename>' on a terminal window could be an option.

- insert into files values
  (nextval('files_seq'), null,'Sample_document.docx',decode('', 'base64'),
  'SUBMITTED',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'1 kB');
- insert into reference_files values
  (currval('files_seq'), 'Sample_document.docx', 'TASK_TEMPLATE_FILE');
